DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260729
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260730
SUMMARY:Deadline: Project Liberty: Co-Lab Fund Micro-Grants (Round 2\, 2026
 )
DESCRIPTION:MEMBERS ONLY: this is a member-led collaboration fund\, not an 
 open public call. Projects must be led by a Project Liberty Coalition (All
 iance) member organization. Round 2 shifts to micro-grants of USD 10\,000 
 or less\, an iterative change from Round 1 intended to spread support acro
 ss more of the Coalition\; organizations that did not receive a Round 1 aw
 ard are preferred. SCOPE: micro-grants fund two kinds of work\, (1) discre
 te projects that strengthen the Coalition itself\, such as Shared Services
  or convenings\, and (2) time-sensitive collaborative projects within a de
 signated workstream. In both cases the work should begin quickly and produ
 ce something concrete. A STRONG APPLICATION SHOWS: work that builds the Co
 alition as an entity\, such as shared tools\, infrastructure or connection
 s that make joint action easier\; clear alignment with a Coalition workstr
 eam\; value for multiple Coalition organizations\; a strong case that the 
 work would not happen\, or would move more slowly\, without the Fund\; a c
 oncrete outcome such as a tool\, resource\, convening\, campaign or resear
 ch product\; and readiness to begin substantive work within two weeks of a
 pproval. LIMIT: one application per organization\, submitted through the e
 xisting Co-Lab Fund application form. Round 1 results were still pending a
 t the time of this call\, with funded projects to be shared soon and engag
 ement opportunities expected across the work. Prospective applicants unsur
 e whether an idea fits this round are invited to reach out first. DEADLINE
 : 29 July 2026 at midnight. Background on the Co-Lab program is in the Coa
 lition's overview document.\n\nOrganisation: Project Liberty (Alliance Ste
 erCo)\; pooled fund supported by Future of Life Institute\, Omidyar Networ
 k\, Ergo Impact\, and Project Liberty\nLocation: Members of the Project Li
 berty coalition (Alliance). Projects led by a Coalition member organizatio
 n\; geography otherwise unrestricted.\nAward: Micro-grants of USD 10\,000 
 or less\, a deliberate change from Round 1's larger awards so the Fund rea
 ches more of the Coalition. Preference given to organizations that did not
  receive a Round 1 award. No application fee.\nDuration: Short\, discrete 
 projects. Applicants must be ready to begin substantive work within two we
 eks of approval. This is the final round of the summer\; the Fund is expec
 ted to resume later in 2026.\n\nMore: https://forms.fillout.com/t/6AGEGhTk
 NJus?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://forms.fillout.com/t/6AGEGhTkNJus?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Members of the Project Liberty coalition (Alliance). Projects led 
 by a Coalition member organization\; geography otherwise unrestricted.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:project-liberty-co-lab-fund-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260621
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260622
SUMMARY:Deadline: Project Liberty: Co-Lab Fund Member Collaboration Grants 
 (Round 1\, 2026)
DESCRIPTION:MEMBERS ONLY: this is a member-led collaboration fund\, not an 
 open public call. Projects must be led by a Project Liberty Coalition (All
 iance) member organization. The Co-Lab Fund\, launched by the coalition's 
 Steering Committee (SteerCo)\, supports projects that Coalition members un
 dertake together\, building on the trust and relationships that already ex
 ist within the community so that funding decisions can rest on the strengt
 h of the idea\, the people behind it\, and their track records rather than
  extensive diligence. In exchange for a streamlined process\, grants stay 
 modest and funded teams share their progress with the broader Coalition as
  projects develop\, creating accountability and letting the community lear
 n from what emerges. Two kinds of projects qualify: (1) work that advances
  the Coalition's active workstreams (listed in the application)\, and (2) 
 investment in the Coalition's connective infrastructure\, such as shared s
 ervices and resources that strengthen collective capacity. Eligibility: pr
 ojects must be led by a Coalition member organization\, produce value for 
 more than one Coalition organization\, begin substantive work within a few
  weeks of approval\, and fall within the active workstreams\; full eligibi
 lity details are in the Overview and FAQ document. How it works: monthly r
 ounds are planned until December 2026 or until the funds are disbursed\; t
 he application is designed to take an hour or less once the project's shap
 e is clear\, and decisions are expected within about three weeks of each d
 eadline. This is the first cycle and the Fund is being built as it goes\, 
 so the process is expected to improve each round. Round 1 closes Sunday\, 
 21 June 2026\; further rounds follow\, so there is no need to force an ide
 a into this cycle. Apply via the Fillout application form.\n\nOrganisation
 : Project Liberty (Alliance SteerCo)\; pooled fund supported by Future of 
 Life Institute\, Omidyar Network\, Ergo Impact\, and Project Liberty\nLoca
 tion: Members of the Project Liberty coalition (Alliance). Projects led by
  a Coalition member organization\; geography otherwise unrestricted.\nAwar
 d: Grants cap at USD 250\,000 per project\; most first-round awards fall b
 etween USD 25\,000 and USD 100\,000. Pooled fund supported by Future of Li
 fe Institute\, Omidyar Network\, Ergo Impact\, and Project Liberty. No app
 lication fee.\nDuration: Project length varies. Funding rounds run monthly
  until December 2026\, or until the funds are disbursed\; decisions are ex
 pected within roughly three weeks of each deadline.\n\nMore: https://forms
 .fillout.com/t/6AGEGhTkNJus?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medi
 um=referral
URL:https://forms.fillout.com/t/6AGEGhTkNJus?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Members of the Project Liberty coalition (Alliance). Projects led 
 by a Coalition member organization\; geography otherwise unrestricted.
END:VEVENT
